					<div class="post-body" itemprop="articleBody">
						<p>Google&#8217;s Gboard keyboard has been picking up a bunch of new features over the past several days, and now, it&#8217;s rolling out another. Real-time translation is coming to Gboard for voice dictation, and it&#8217;s rolling out now for Android users.</p>
<p><span id="more-372426"></span><ins class="adsbygoogle author_ad"
			style="display:block;"
			data-ad-host="ca-host-pub-5506057612223327"
			data-ad-client="ca-pub-8513483021683571"
			data-ad-format="auto"></ins>
		<script>
			(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
		</script></p>
<p>Confirmed to <em><a href="https://www.androidpolice.com/2020/08/11/gboard-rolls-out-real-time-transcription-and-translation-apk-download/">Android Police</a></em>, Google says that this real-time translation and transcription feature is heading to every Android smartphone with the latest Gboard updates. The company had previously made quiet mention of the feature in a changelog, but it never rolled out to users before today. </p>
<p>Gboard has offered translation <a href="https://9to5google.com/2017/03/02/gboard-6-1-update-beta-translate-themes/">for about three years now</a>, but the feature only worked for text being manually typed. Still handy, but it locked out the users who rely on voice transcription on a regular basis. Now, that&#8217;s changing. A simple tap of the microphone icon when you&#8217;re using Gboard&#8217;s translation feature (Gboard &gt; Overflow menu &gt; Translate) will see anything you say transcribed in the language of your choosing.</p>
<p>As seen below, this can be handy for replying to a message in another language, but it could also be used for transcribing another user&#8217;s words into an app like Google Keep without constantly jumping back and forth between the full Google Translate app. Apparently, this feature also works with the hands-free UI <a href="https://9to5google.com/2020/08/09/gboard-hands-free-typing/">that we detailed over the weekend</a></p>
<div class="wp-block-image is-style-default">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img data-attachment-id="372434" data-permalink="https://9to5google.com/2020/08/11/gboard-translation-voice-transcription/gboard_translation_voice_1/" data-orig-file="https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2020/08/gboard_translation_voice_1.gif" data-orig-size="800,1644" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="gboard_translation_voice_1" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2020/08/gboard_translation_voice_1.gif?w=341" data-large-file="https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2020/08/gboard_translation_voice_1.gif?w=498" title="Gboard&#039;s real-time translation feature now works with your voice" loading="lazy" src="https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2020/08/gboard_translation_voice_1.gif?w=498" alt="" class="wp-image-372434" width="374" height="767" /></figure>
</div>
<p>This handy new feature is available on Gboard for all Android phones, but it seems it may require a server-side change. It should work, though, on both beta and stable versions of the keyboard.</p>
